      "self_limiting": "Telogen effluvium from a single trigger is self-limiting \u2014 resolves in 6 to 12 months once trigger is removed. Chronic telogen effluvium (persisting more than 6 months) indicates persistent nutritional or hormonal cause.",
      "lag_explanation": "Hair is always shed 2 to 3 months after the triggering event because that is how long telogen lasts. Iron supplementation started today will not show hair results for 3 to 4 months."
    },
